00:50:46.511 --> 00:50:50.940
So the story-- it turns out that neurologically,
there is a way to measure happiness, which

00:50:50.940 --> 00:50:52.509
is very surprising.

00:50:52.509 --> 00:50:58.299
It's a very simple way which is they measure
the relative activation of the left prefrontal

00:50:58.299 --> 00:51:01.450
cortex over here, a specific part of the brain.

00:51:01.450 --> 00:51:04.710
And then versus the right prefrontal cortex.

00:51:04.710 --> 00:51:13.499
It turns out that if the left-right tilt,
if it's more left than right, the first person

00:51:13.499 --> 00:51:16.300
experiences "I'm happy, I'm optimistic, I'm
joyful" and so on.

00:51:16.300 --> 00:51:17.530
Positive stuff.

00:51:17.530 --> 00:51:22.039
And the more the grade is, the more positive
the person's reports.

00:51:22.039 --> 00:51:24.619
And vice versa.

00:51:24.619 --> 00:51:26.220
Why is that so?

00:51:26.220 --> 00:51:30.729
Nobody knows for sure, but there is a very
important clue, which is only the left prefrontal

00:51:30.729 --> 00:51:34.380
cortex here has a direct connection to the
amygdala.

00:51:34.380 --> 00:51:38.109
So only that part has the ability to tone
down the negativity.

00:51:38.109 --> 00:51:39.890
This part doesn't have that.

00:51:39.890 --> 00:51:41.719
It's not clear why.

00:51:41.719 --> 00:51:44.539
There is a relationship.

00:51:44.539 --> 00:51:48.569
This data has been around long enough, has
been studied for long enough, that there is

00:51:48.569 --> 00:51:52.769
